<br>
Currently, I have a Shaped Shadewood Compound bow (range 200)<br>
I use class 2 arrows with a range of 150.<br>
<br>
Nice 350 range...I can hit mobs halfway across the zone and occasionally, to my annoyance, have actually had to go fetch the mob because I shot it from outside the aggro radius.<br>
<br>
The situations I don't use a bow:<br>
<br>
Multi-level zones where &quot;Target is too far above/below you&quot;<br>
When I run out of arrows<br>
When I've shot at the mob 3 times without a response because I have a terrible 75 archery skill.  (lol)  Then I just get fed up and cast &quot;cease&quot; on it.<br>
<br>
<br>
I like the bow because it does have a longer range than my spells and if you're in a competitive zone that might be the difference between you getting the mob or that druid over there.<br>
